Forming Plurals In French
Generally, you form plurals in French in the same
way you do in English. IE: By adding an s.
However, words that end in the letter "u"
will use "x" instead of "s" as a plural ending.
EG
Singular       Plural
un pull        des pulls
une chaussette des chaussettes
un eleve       des eleves
le sac         les sacs
la jupe        les jupes
l'enfant       les enfants
If a word ends in -s, then there is no change in
the plural.
EG
Singular       Plural
Une souris     Des souris
What do un and une change to in the plural?
What happens to le, la and l'?
A few words have a special plural ening in -x
Like the -s ending, it is not spoken
Singular       Plural
un cadeau      des cadeaux
un jeu         des jeux
un animal      des animaux
